What is a CRM
Customer relationship management (CRM) is a technology for managing all your company's relationships and interactions with customers and potential customers.

What is LSA 
Latent semantic analysis is a technique in natural language processing, in particular distributional semantics, of analyzing relationships between a set of documents
and the terms they contain by producing a set of concepts related to the documents and terms.

What is CPA
Cost per Acquisition is a metric in digital marketing to determine the amount of assets invested to convert audience into a number of paying customers for your business.

What is AMPHTML
AMP is an open source HTML framework which loads faster and is optimized for safer ad displays.

What is ROAS
ROAS (return on ad spend) is a a marketing metric to measure the returns or sales one makes over a particular amount of investment in marketing and advertising.
Values:
-ROAS< 3 ( change and access the current marketing campaign)
-ROAS> 5 ( stick to the current plan and aim on boosting)

What is MAN
MAN is used in selling for qualifying new prospects. It questions Money, Authority and Need to buy.

What is ICP
ICP or Ideal Customer Profile is a hypothetical decription of the type of company that would reap the most benefit from your product or solution.
